payload.description: Demonstration of the Leap Motion as input for Godot Engine.

release.name: Hackathon-v1.0
release.body:
Version planned for demonstration at Hack K-State.

Requirements
- Leap Motion Hardware
- [Leap Motion SDK](https://developer.leapmotion.com/windows-vr)
- OpenGL ES 3.0 Compatible GPU

Extract the files and tun ```Digitalis.exe``` to try it out.

commits.message: Graphical improvements to lightning and ground
Added Locator_Grid in Resources for baseplate.
Added audio playback in main through child nodes Crackle and Chimes.
Added Wind chimes sound effect for tracers
Particle effects for fireball and trail
Added basics of particle trail effect
Added functioning sliders for X, Y, Z.
Added basic GUI elements (broken slider, working console window)

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/ectucker1/Fluid
Merge remote changes
